- Shep, I'm so stupid.

04:28.367 --> 04:30.700
- [chuckles]
- Like, why am I so forthcoming?

04:30.700 --> 04:32.066
It's like she never
would have known that.

04:32.066 --> 04:33.367
- No.
- You know?

04:33.367 --> 04:34.767
And it's such a minute,
you know, detail.

04:34.767 --> 04:36.367
- Yeah.
- Doesn't even need to be said.

04:36.367 --> 04:38.633
- But it's like from
a romantic comedy, you know?

04:38.633 --> 04:40.166
Spin around,
pick up the...

04:40.166 --> 04:42.200
- And she hung on that,
and was like,

04:42.200 --> 04:43.700
"You didn't spin me around
when I got there."

04:43.700 --> 04:45.233
And I was like...

04:45.233 --> 04:49.266
And, Shep, she, uh,
she tossed a drink at me.

04:49.266 --> 04:51.000
- In you--on you?

04:51.000 --> 04:52.000
- Boom.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.100
And I was like,

04:53.100 --> 04:55.600
"You get in an Uber
and go home."

04:55.600 --> 04:58.500
And it's been
radio silence since.

04:58.500 --> 05:01.066
- She hasn't texted you once?

05:01.066 --> 05:03.100
- I blocked her.

05:03.100 --> 05:05.066
- You blocked her?
- Yeah.

05:05.066 --> 05:07.400
Breakups are normally
pretty hard for me.

05:07.400 --> 05:09.767
But, like, she made it
crystal clear for me:

05:09.767 --> 05:11.100
We are over.

05:11.100 --> 05:14.200
And I have no remorse.

05:14.200 --> 05:15.266
It's called trust.
- Yeah.

05:15.266 --> 05:17.000
- You know, I'm not over here

05:17.000 --> 05:18.767
to send any sort of
wrong messages to anyone.

05:18.767 --> 05:21.600
- Wouldn't it be crazy
if, before Christmas,

05:21.600 --> 05:24.333
everybody was just
dead-ass single?

05:24.333 --> 05:26.000
- What do you want
for Christmas?

05:26.000 --> 05:28.333
A stable relationship.
- [chuckles] No, no.

05:28.333 --> 05:30.567
