for making time for me.

05:49.567 --> 05:51.567
- Absolutely.
- I really appreciate this.

05:51.567 --> 05:53.533
- It's my pleasure.
- I know how busy you are.

05:53.533 --> 05:56.300
Like, I feel so lucky that
you can squeeze me in, so...

05:56.300 --> 05:58.367
- No, I'm happy to.

05:58.367 --> 06:01.300
- I know how precious,
how valuable your time is.

06:01.300 --> 06:04.166
- How's your, uh--
it sounds a little hoarse.

06:04.166 --> 06:05.433
- Sounds--yeah.

06:05.433 --> 06:07.567
- You need a hot toddy
for your throat.

06:07.567 --> 06:09.233
[bell clanging]
- I will--[laughs]

06:09.233 --> 06:11.233
- Let me get Michael in here.
- Yes, madam?

06:11.233 --> 06:14.600
- Michael, we need
two medicinal drinks.

06:14.600 --> 06:17.033
A hot toddy for the young lady.

06:17.033 --> 06:18.200
- The same for you, madam?

06:18.200 --> 06:20.066
- My martini.
- Very good.

06:20.066 --> 06:22.200
- Thank you.
So what's been going on?

06:22.200 --> 06:25.033
- [sighs] You know, the--
when I--when we went shopping,

06:25.033 --> 06:26.734
we were making a joke
'cause of your ring.

06:26.734 --> 06:29.533
I was saying, you know, "Next
time let's go ring shopping."

06:29.533 --> 06:30.734
Instead of clothing shopping...

06:30.734 --> 06:33.266
- How's that going, by the way?

06:33.266 --> 06:35.467
- Let's just say that we
pumped the break a little bit.

06:35.467 --> 06:37.333
- How so?

06:37.333 --> 06:41.000
- It's hard to talk about
without getting too emotional.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.066
Since moving over here,
you know,

06:43.066 --> 06:44.600
it's been such a transition
and--[sniffs]

06:44.600 --> 06:48.066
Thomas is really,
you know, all I have.

06:48.066 --> 06:50.200
I know you've heard
a little bit about Hilton Head.

06:50.200 --> 06:52.200
- All I've heard is
all hell broke loose--

06:52.200 --> 06:53.600
- Yes.
- And... you know.

06:53.600 --> 06:56.700
- Yes.
We had some confrontation with--

06:56.700 --> 06:58.767
with the mother of
Thomas' children.

06:58.767 --> 07:00.633
I see those children
more than you see them.

07:00.633 --> 07:02.600
How many times did you go
visit your son in the hospital?

07:02.600 --> 07:05.600
- Whoa, dude.
- Yeah. Yeah!

07:05.600 --> 07:09.467
You know, after that,
tension started building.

07:09.467 --> 07:13.033
I felt a shift
in my relationship.

07:13.033 --> 07:14.567
As soon as we came back,

07:14.567 --> 07:16.567
she had sent him a text saying,

07:16.567 --> 07:20.166
"I don't feel safe with
our children around Ashley.

07:20.166 --> 07:23.033
She's hateful and angry,"

07:23.033 --> 07:24.367
and that really hurt.

07:24.367 --> 07:26.100
This is the family
that I have out here.

07:26.100 --> 07:28.233
These kids, they've been
like family to me too...

07:28.233 --> 07:29.734
- [clears throat]
- Thank you so much.

07:29.734 --> 07:32.233
- You can just set it
on that book is fine.

07:32.233 --> 07:34.367
He makes them strong,
but they do the job.

07:34.367 --> 07:35.667
- But it--it does the job.

07:35.667 --> 07:37.233
