See what you think.

07:37.233 --> 07:38.667
- Thank you so much. Okay.
- It is hot.

07:38.667 --> 07:41.533
- How long have you been sick?
- Ten days.

07:41.533 --> 07:43.133
Yeah. My immune system...

07:43.133 --> 07:45.000
- Do you think your
immune system is run down?

07:45.000 --> 07:47.367
- I'm stressed.
I don't know what to do.

07:47.367 --> 07:51.400
'Cause I've picked up my life
and come here.

07:51.400 --> 07:53.233
Sometimes I cry and I say,

07:53.233 --> 07:54.767
"Is this what I envisioned
for my life?"

07:54.767 --> 07:57.533
- Is he still partying...
- All the time.

07:57.533 --> 07:59.400
I know he's out right now.

07:59.400 --> 08:02.066
And so, I'm also dealing with,
you know, an older man

08:02.066 --> 08:04.000
that just--I feel like--

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
I'm like,
"Get your sh-- together."

08:07.000 --> 08:10.233
- Well, let me tell you
something that I've learned

08:10.233 --> 08:14.133
from my 105 years here on Earth.
- Yeah.

08:14.133 --> 08:18.266
- Is that--
first of all, men don't change.

08:18.266 --> 08:21.633
Now, in terms of
managing Thomas?

08:21.633 --> 08:27.133
Feminists are not
gonna like this word of advice.

08:27.133 --> 08:29.567
Just sit there and listen.

08:29.567 --> 08:34.433
Down south we just don't
get into these issues.

08:34.433 --> 08:36.367
And, as my mother used to say,

08:36.367 --> 08:39.433
"Keep quiet and
just think of England."

08:39.433 --> 08:41.433
Make it about him.

08:41.433 --> 08:43.133
- It's always about him,
Patricia.

08:43.133 --> 08:44.567
It always--
- It's always about him.

08:44.567 --> 08:46.033
But you know what?
- Always.

08:46.033 --> 08:49.166
- If you were secure,
let it be about him.

08:49.166 --> 08:53.433
The other thing is that
Kathryn is going to be

08:53.433 --> 08:57.166
