27:02.633 --> 27:04.667
- Hey, Craigy.
- How are ya?

27:04.667 --> 27:06.233
both: Mwuah.

27:06.233 --> 27:07.400
- How nice.

27:07.400 --> 27:09.266
- Oh.
One broke on the way over.

27:09.266 --> 27:11.266
- Come sit down over there...
- Sure, sure.

27:11.266 --> 27:13.066
- And let me put these down.

27:13.066 --> 27:15.667
So what happened to your hand?

27:15.667 --> 27:18.600
- I severed my tendon
in my pinky.

27:18.600 --> 27:20.200
It's slowing me down
a little bit,

27:20.200 --> 27:21.767
but I'm getting used to it.

27:21.767 --> 27:25.633
- So, unfortunately,
we're in a time crunch.

27:25.633 --> 27:27.100
- Um.

27:27.100 --> 27:29.266
I had fabrics,

27:29.266 --> 27:31.633
'cause they look
a little different now.

27:31.633 --> 27:33.667
- You know what, the fabrics

27:33.667 --> 27:35.400
really don't
make any difference.

27:35.400 --> 27:38.100
It's the design
that's really the key.

27:38.100 --> 27:39.133
[playfully tense music]

27:39.133 --> 27:40.333
- Well, I guess...

27:40.333 --> 27:42.133
[mutters]
I might as well show you.

27:42.133 --> 27:43.533
- Please.

27:43.533 --> 27:45.133
- Here's the--
- Turn it around this way.

27:45.133 --> 27:46.133
So I can...

27:46.133 --> 27:47.567
- Here's a very simple one.

27:47.567 --> 27:49.166
- Now, that's cute.

27:49.166 --> 27:51.300
- I actually have
a full rendition

27:51.300 --> 27:53.133
on my phone.

27:53.133 --> 27:55.033
- Let's see.

27:55.033 --> 27:58.367
How did you do the dogs?

27:58.367 --> 28:02.567
- Um, there was a stencil
that I found online.

28:02.567 --> 28:05.100
And then I did the colors.

28:05.100 --> 28:08.533
- You can't get anything
off the internet.

28:08.533 --> 28:10.667
- Mm-hmm.
- It just has to be original.

28:10.667 --> 28:12.300
- You just need
something to start with,

28:12.300 --> 28:14.033
and then you can feed off it.

28:14.033 --> 28:15.700
And that's why I didn't
really know where to start.

28:15.700 --> 28:19.033
- But, you know,
it should be drawn better

28:19.033 --> 28:21.700
so that it doesn't
look like clip art.

28:21.700 --> 28:25.000
- You know, I'll start
playing around with things more.

28:25.000 --> 28:27.467
- Our problem right now
is timing.

28:27.467 --> 28:30.734
- But do you have
a direction

28:30.734 --> 28:32.667
that I should concentrate on?

28:32.667 --> 28:36.333
- But we had to have
the design right now.

28:36.333 --> 28:38.266
- Well, yeah, I just--
I wasn't aware of that.

28:38.266 --> 28:40.567
What do you think I have?
Ten days to do it?

28:40.567 --> 28:42.033
- Couple of weeks.

28:42.033 --> 28:44.567
It's been two months.

28:44.567 --> 28:47.667
I mean, we really could have
had this conversation

28:47.667 --> 28:50.066
two months ago.

28:50.066 --> 28:51.533
I mean, I love you.

28:51.533 --> 28:54.300
I've given you more latitude

28:54.300 --> 28:56.734
than I would ordinarily...
- Right.

28:56.734 --> 29:01.266
- But I think
we have to table it.

29:01.266 --> 29:03.333
It's business, you know?

29:03.333 --> 29:04.433
Uh...
- Yeah.

29:04.433 --> 29:06.000
And now, I'm gonna see what, uh,

29:06.000 --> 29:08.767
you know, I think--
I--I, uh...

29:08.767 --> 29:12.633
I hadn't done animal stuff
until we started talking.

29:12.633 --> 29:14.500
And maybe, you know,
I should of,

29:14.500 --> 29:16.500
uh, put more time on this.

29:16.500 --> 29:18.767
- Right.
Exactly.

29:18.767 --> 29:21.233
- Um.
All right, well, thank you.

29:21.233 --> 29:23.100
You know, it didn't
work out this time,

29:23.100 --> 29:25.233
and who knows where we'll be
in a few months or whatnot.

29:25.233 --> 29:28.433
If I had one more night
to work on these designs,

29:28.433 --> 29:31.233
I can make them perfect;
and I know she'd love them.

29:31.233 --> 29:32.633
All right.

29:32.633 --> 29:34.233
- Thank you.

29:34.233 --> 29:36.700
♪ ♪

29:39.700 --> 29:41.367
- Coming up...

29:41.367 --> 29:45.233
- I've been doing my best
to make you mine.

29:45.233 --> 29:46.333
- [gasps]

29:49.533 --> 29:50.100
[upbeat jazzy music]

29:52.367 --> 29:58.133
♪ ♪

29:58.133 --> 29:59.133
- [exhales]

29:59.133 --> 30:00.667
Naomie!

30:00.667 --> 30:02.667
- Yeah?
- Little help?

30:02.667 --> 30:04.533
- Oh--
- Oh, my God, that's heavy.

30:04.533 --> 30:06.667
- I got so much food.

30:06.667 --> 30:08.633
- Oh, my gosh,
you got fruit, salad...

30:08.633 --> 30:09.633
- Nugs.

30:09.633 --> 30:11.533
- [gasps]
Cam loves nugs.

30:11.533 --> 30:13.000
Yeah, I got people to come over,

30:13.000 --> 30:15.000
like, a manicurist,
a masseuse.

30:15.000 --> 30:16.400
- I'm so excited.

30:16.400 --> 30:18.400
- So I gotta tell you
about our day yesterday.

30:18.400 --> 30:21.266
We were so worried about
where the hell Kathryn was.

30:21.266 --> 30:22.533
- What's the deal?

30:22.533 --> 30:24.266
- So Danni and I
drove over there.

30:24.266 --> 30:25.667
She obviously
didn't answer the door,

30:25.667 --> 30:27.667
so we went to
the office, or whatever,

30:27.667 --> 30:29.266
asked them to do
a wellness check.

30:29.266 --> 30:31.033
She said, "I can just
tell you she's alive,

30:31.033 --> 30:33.567
and I can't give any more
details than that."

30:33.567 --> 30:35.400
- What in the world?

30:35.400 --> 30:37.700
I think what's hard is, like,
when you care about someone

30:37.700 --> 30:41.400
and you want to help them
and there's nothing you can do.

30:41.400 --> 30:43.433
- I don't know, I just
feel so bad for her.

30:43.433 --> 30:45.166
- Let's make a drink.
- Yeah.

30:45.166 --> 30:46.433
- Sweet tea.
I don't want liquor.

30:46.433 --> 30:47.700
- Yeah, I don't
want any alcohol.

30:47.700 --> 30:50.166
- Me either.
[knocking on door]

30:50.166 --> 30:51.567
- Hi.
- Hey.

30:51.567 --> 30:53.400
- How are y'all doing?
- Good, good, good.

30:53.400 --> 30:55.166
- We're so happy y'all are here.

30:55.166 --> 30:57.400
Is there any way we could just
test out the massages?

30:57.400 --> 30:59.166
- Sure.
- Grease me up.

30:59.166 --> 31:01.567
[light music]

31:01.567 --> 31:03.700
I can tell you got good hands.

31:03.700 --> 31:05.567
- My gosh, I just want
a blanket and my cat

31:05.567 --> 31:06.700
and I'm in Heaven.

31:06.700 --> 31:08.166
[knocking on door]

31:08.166 --> 31:10.166
- Hi. Look at y'all.
- Hi.

31:10.166 --> 31:12.400
- We're just testing 'em out
for y'all.

31:12.400 --> 31:13.600
- I cannot wait
to get a manicure.

31:13.600 --> 31:16.333
I have paint, like,
all in my nails.

31:16.333 --> 31:19.433
- Have you heard from Kathryn?
- Nope.

31:19.433 --> 31:21.600
- Me neither.

31:21.600 --> 31:23.300
You look like
you're taking a sh--.

31:23.300 --> 31:24.734
[laughter]

31:24.734 --> 31:27.200
[knocking on door]
Come in!

31:27.200 --> 31:28.734
- I'm free!
[all cheering]

31:28.734 --> 31:31.033
I'm free! I'm free!

31:31.033 --> 31:32.567
- Oh, my God.
- What--look at you!

31:32.567 --> 31:34.600
- You look just like you did
before you--

31:34.600 --> 31:36.433
- Shut up.
- I know.

31:36.433 --> 31:37.700
That's some bullsh--.
- You did not just have a baby.

31:37.700 --> 31:39.333
I don't believe it.
- Yes, I did.

31:39.333 --> 31:41.066
- Oh, my gosh.
- Take my spot, here.

31:41.066 --> 31:43.300
- If I squeeze too hard,
what's gonna happen?

31:43.300 --> 31:44.734
- You might get squirted
in the face.

31:44.734 --> 31:46.734
- Can I touch your boobs?
Can I touch 'em?

31:46.734 --> 31:48.467
- Pull 'em out.
Let's see 'em.

31:48.467 --> 31:51.066
- Oh, my gosh.
They're, like, solid.

31:51.066 --> 31:52.467
- 'Cause they're full of milk.

31:52.467 --> 31:55.100
- So Chelsea has
a business opportunity for you.

31:55.100 --> 31:57.467
- Have you ever heard of people
selling their breast milk?

31:57.467 --> 31:58.467
- Selling it?
- Yes.

31:58.467 --> 32:00.100
- I think people donate it.

32:00.100 --> 32:01.233
You'd probably feel like
an asshole to sell it.

32:01.233 --> 32:03.233
- No, people buy it.

32:03.233 --> 32:04.633
- You could sell it
for a lot of money.

32:04.633 --> 32:05.633
- What?
- Yes!

32:05.633 --> 32:07.633
Let me be your manager!

32:07.633 --> 32:10.100
- Well, I have an oversupply,
so let's get rich.

32:10.100 --> 32:11.767
- That's what I'm talking about.

32:11.767 --> 32:13.633
- Okay, I want to know--I want
to just know all the things.

32:13.633 --> 32:14.767
- Do you want me to massage
your hands while you're talking?

32:14.767 --> 32:16.633
- Oh, girl, yes.
- Kay.

32:16.633 --> 32:19.233
- Okay, I want to know
the high and the low.

32:19.233 --> 32:20.767
- The low is--

32:20.767 --> 32:22.467
oh, my God, this is Heaven--

32:22.467 --> 32:24.633
your life revolves around
this little being,

32:24.633 --> 32:28.100
and you are forced to be
unselfish.

32:28.100 --> 32:31.433
And the high is
you have this little baby that

32:31.433 --> 32:34.200
is, like, part of you
and part of your partner.

32:34.200 --> 32:35.734
- Mm-hmm.

32:35.734 --> 32:37.400
- And you just have
unconditional love for it.

32:37.400 --> 32:39.266
And you'll do anything for her.

32:39.266 --> 32:41.533
Palmer, she has smiled
at me for the first time.

32:41.533 --> 32:45.266
And believe it or not,
I cried.

32:45.266 --> 32:49.100
My heart is not cold and dead
after all.

32:49.100 --> 32:50.667
[bottle pops]
- Yeah, baby.

32:50.667 --> 32:52.133
- Oh, my God, I'm so excited.

32:52.133 --> 32:54.133
I'm gonna get a buzz
off of two sips.

32:54.133 --> 32:56.100
- So now you have to
pump alcohol out of you?

32:56.100 --> 32:57.767
- Mm-hmm.
- Let's bottle it up.

32:57.767 --> 32:59.266
[laughter]

32:59.266 --> 33:01.000
- Who wants their feet rubbed?

33:01.000 --> 33:02.367
- Okay, rub my feet.
- Get your feet rubbed.

33:02.367 --> 33:04.266
[laughter]

33:04.266 --> 33:05.667
- Feels great.

33:05.667 --> 33:08.266
- Naomie, will you grab
her ultrasound thing?

33:08.266 --> 33:10.266
I can, like,
kind of recognize her in this.

33:10.266 --> 33:11.333
- Can you?

33:11.333 --> 33:13.133
[cymbal shimmers]

33:13.133 --> 33:14.667
Oh!

33:14.667 --> 33:16.734
Danni, that is seriously
a treasure.

33:16.734 --> 33:19.433
Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

33:19.433 --> 33:21.100
- Okay, you can stop.

33:21.100 --> 33:23.300
I've gotta go, I really do.
Damn.

33:23.300 --> 33:27.300
I'm definitely learning
balance in my life right now.

33:27.300 --> 33:30.166
Still having my own life,
but at the same time,

33:30.166 --> 33:32.166
being a good mother to Palmer.

33:32.166 --> 33:34.300
I'm 15 minutes past my curfew.

33:34.300 --> 33:37.266
This is my new life.
There's no going back.

33:37.266 --> 33:38.700
Love you. [kisses]
- Goodbye.

33:38.700 --> 33:40.567
- It's no longer about me.

33:40.567 --> 33:43.700
And I think it's
a lesson that I needed to learn.

33:43.700 --> 33:45.300
- We need to do this more often.

33:45.300 --> 33:46.667
- [kisses]
- See you later.

33:46.667 --> 33:48.133
- Love you.
- Love you too.

33:48.133 --> 33:49.433
[door shuts]

33:49.433 --> 33:51.700
[cell phone ringing]

33:51.700 --> 33:53.300
- Shepard.

33:53.300 --> 33:55.166
- Hello, Miss Chelsea.

34:03.600 --> 34:04.700
- Good.
